## The `.svx` law and ratchet

**Verdict: `wobbly`.** The checker is real, but enforcement is narrow.

`dark-wizard/scripts/check-brain-svx.sh` finds `.md` files under any `.brain`,
then subtracts a repo-root `.brain-svx-baseline` (or the legacy
`.brain/.svx-lint-baseline`). Baselines exist only in `dark-wizard`,
`joelclaw`, and `joelclaw-wiki`.

Only `joelclaw-wiki/package.json` wires the checker into its normal lint command
through `lint:brain`. The registered roots contain 19 `.md` files; 18 are
ratcheted. `joelclaw` currently fails because
`.brain/data/grill-master/joelclaw-wiki-v0-claude-prompt.md` is not in its
baseline, while the baseline still carries an old path that no longer exists.
Across all 31 trees, 11 of the 29 `.md` files are unratcheted violations in five
trees.

Receipts:

- `~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/scripts/check-brain-svx.sh`
- `dark-wizard/.brain-svx-baseline`
- `joelclaw/.brain-svx-baseline`
- `joelclaw-wiki/.brain-svx-baseline`
- `joelclaw-wiki/package.json` (`lint` → `lint:brain`)

## Registry and audit

**Verdict: `working`.** Membership is explicit, and the audit treats orphans as
proposals rather than silently ingesting them.

`brain-roots.json` now names `user`, `joelclaw`, `observer`, and `wiki`.
`observer` was added by the sibling session at commit `e03b805`, as expected by
this task. The live static site has not rebuilt from that registry yet:
`/user/index/`, `/joelclaw/index/`, and `/wiki/index/` returned 200, while
`/observer/index/` returned 404.

The live `/graph/` page returned 200. It is an honest registered-root index and
registry-audit view, not the graph projection. Its current audit reports 49
unregistered candidates from blaine, but flagg's crawl hit its 45-second limit.
That is why the live audit and this exact local 31-tree scan answer different
questions.

Receipts:

- `~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/brain-roots.json`
- `~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/brain-roots-audit.json`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/routes/graph/+page.server.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/routes/graph/+page.svelte`
- live checks against `https://brain.joelclaw.com/graph/` and the four root index URLs

## How a file becomes a URL

**Renderer verdict: `working`.** The three previously deployed roots render;
the new observer root is waiting on the next static build.

1. `brain-roots.json` assigns a root name, checkout, and `.brain` path.
2. `catalog.ts` walks only `.svx` files. It drops any path containing
   `captures`, `compaction-dumps`, `people`, or `private-family-health`, and it
   drops pages whose frontmatter is exactly `privacy: sensitive`.
3. The relative path loses `.svx`. For example,
   `.brain/resources/fleet-sync-doctrine.svx` becomes the key
   `user/resources/fleet-sync-doctrine` and the URL
   `/user/resources/fleet-sync-doctrine/`.
4. The Vite `virtual:brain-pages` plugin resolves wikilinks, injects component
   imports, compiles MDSvX, then checks the generated Svelte. Component lookup
   is project-local `.brain/components/**` first, then wiki standard/shared
   components. A broken page becomes a page-scoped compile-error card instead
   of killing every page.
5. `[root]/[...slug]/+page.server.ts` prerenders one route per catalog entry,
   renders the compiled module, adds repo/path/commit provenance, and asks the
   graph reader for a local neighborhood.
6. The live site changes only after the wiki is rebuilt and published. A
   registry commit by itself does not add a live route.

Receipts:

- `joelclaw-wiki/src/lib/brain/catalog.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/lib/brain/vite-plugin.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/routes/[root]/[...slug]/+page.server.ts`

## Brain Graph

**Verdict: `wobbly`.** The projection and neighborhood UI exist, but the data is
manual and stale.

The active Brain Graph brief has shipped the registry, multi-root projection,
renderer, graph quality baseline, and Pi change ledger. Three steps remain open:
agent query surface, cross-root navigation's Joel-use verdict, and retirement
of the old Studio viewer.

`graph-builder.ts` reads the registry's `.svx` pages, Git commit provenance,
frontmatter parents, wikilinks, and edition JSON. It emits brain-page/section,
edition, observation, open-loop, project, and unresolved-page nodes plus
containment, parent, wikilink, evidence, project, and source-observation edges.
It also audits unregistered first-level repo brains.

The current ignored `joelclaw-wiki/data/graph.json` is schema v3, **932 nodes / 805
edges**, over only `user`, `joelclaw`, and `wiki`. Its filesystem mtime is
2026-07-12 13:38 PDT. It predates the observer registration and five days of
Brain writes. The normal wiki `build` script does not rebuild it. The live
`/graph/` route does not read it; individual Brain pages do read it for
backlinks and local neighborhoods.

Receipts:

- `joelclaw/.brain/projects/brain-graph/brain-graph-brief.svx`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/lib/services/graph-builder.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/src/lib/services/graph-read.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/scripts/build-graph.ts`
- `joelclaw-wiki/data/graph.json`

## Fleet sync

**Verdict: `working`.** The transport and symlink are correct; active dirty work
still cannot travel until its owner commits and pushes it.

`dw-sync.sh` fetches and fast-forwards `origin/main`, refuses divergence, reports
ahead/behind state, and limits staging to durable surfaces. At 10:01 PDT,
dark-wizard `HEAD` and the local `origin/main` both pointed at `3d40124`; the
last fetch was 10:00:54 PDT. There were 17 dirty paths, 15 on durable surfaces,
from active sessions. That is in-flight state, not committed fleet memory.

Receipts:

- `~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard/scripts/dw-sync.sh`
- `git -C ~/Code/joelhooks/dark-wizard status/log/reflog`
- `~/.brain` symlink target

## Three load-bearing risks

1. **A graph rebuild can leak sensitive metadata.** The renderer excludes four
   sections and `privacy: sensitive`, but `graph-builder.ts` does not. It reads
   every `.svx` under registered roots and merely copies privacy fields onto
   nodes. `graph-read.ts`, `Backlinks.svelte`, and `LocalGraph.svelte` do not
   filter those nodes before printing labels and provenance. The stale graph
   currently has zero sensitive nodes; rebuilding against today's user Brain
   would ingest hundreds unless this boundary is fixed first.
2. **Freshness depends on a human remembering two different builds.** The static
   page catalog refreshes only on wiki build/publish, while `graph.json` has its
   own manual builder and is not part of `package.json`'s build script. The
   observer root is the live proof: registered locally, still 404; the graph is
   older still.
3. **The law and the registry cover only a small slice of physical reality.**
   Four of 31 trees render, only one repo runs the `.svx` checker during lint,
   and 11 `.md` files are outside any ratchet. Orphans are not inherently wrong,
   but right now there is no single gate proving each orphan is intentionally
   local, intentionally archived, or waiting for registration.
